div.div:
(1) Initialize state
**** Commits ****
commits: [Object]
The list of commits obtained from props
[
{
commitId: string
committer: string,
timestamp: string,
message: string
}
]
selectedCommit: string
The commit id that was selected
**** All Files ****
allFiles: [Object]
An array holding the name of each file, and the contents of each file
[
{
name: string,
contents: [text_line_by_line]
}, ...
]
**** Selected File Container ****
selectionIndex: number
The index of the file container clicked
numberOfSvgs: number
The number of svg elements for the current file container
minimapMaxHeights: [number]
The max heights for each svg for the current file container
scrollContainerHeight: number
The height of the scroll container for the current file container
**** Active test cases ****
testcases: [Object]
[
{
testcase_name: [
{
testcaseId: string,
signature: string,
passed: number (0|1)
}, ...
]
}, ...
]
**** Fault localization ****
suspiciousness: [Object]
[
{
source: string,
lines: [
{
suspiciousness: number,
hsl: string,
linenumber: number
}, ...
]
}, ...
]
**** Buttons and Dialogs ****
isButtonGroupDisabled: boolean
Determins if the button group (clear, all, passed failed) will be disabled.
isViewScoresDisabled: boolean
Determines if the view scores button will be disabled.
isDialogOpened: boolean
isSuspDialogOpened: boolean
Both determines if the modal dialog will be shown or not.
coverableIndex: number
Represents the index of the tr node that was clicked, which is used for the #dialogSuspContainer

div.div:
Minimap has 3 event listeners to function:
1. mousedown - user clicks on a part of the minimap (current or new)
2. drag - user drags the slider up and down the minimap. User can't drag out of minimap. Event occurs after mousedown.
3. scroll - user scrolls the display view, the scroll container. When the user drags, the scroll container is updated, and when the user scrolls the scroll container, the minimap updates.
(1) Remove all existing sliders and drag behaviors first
(2) Define the state for the slider
1. Base => There is only one rect sliding
2. Transition next => There is the current rect on the minimap and a newly generated rect above the next svg element.
3. Transition back => There is the current rect on the minimap and a newly generated rect below the previous svg element.
The rest is a bit complicated so it's better to check the source code

{

contents: string
}

For each file, generate the minimap.
(4) Update state
- allFiles: [

contents: [string]
},...
]
